# Notifications Frontend

A responsive React + Material UI frontend for the campus notification platform.

## Features

- Displays all notifications with pagination, limit, and type filtering
- Shows a dedicated Priority Inbox for top `n` notifications
- Distinguishes between viewed and new notifications using localStorage
- Uses Material UI for polished styling and responsive layout
- Fetches notifications from the evaluation API via query parameters

## Install

`
``bash
cd "c:\Ankit Mittal\notifications-frontend"
npm install
```

## Run locally

```bash
npm run dev
```

Then open `http://localhost:3007`.

## Build

```bash
npm run build
```

## Notes

- The app expects the notifications API at `http://20.207.122.201/evaluation-service/notifications`
- If the route requires authentication, the browser will attempt to use credentials by default
- Use the `Priority` tab to view the top notifications sorted by type and recency
